Rating: 4
I made this recipe over the weekend and made 1.5x as I had a lot of bread I wanted to use up. I liked the overall flavor, but the custard was a little too thick and didn't get absorbed into all of the bread, even though I let it sit overnight in the refrigerator. I used half and half and whole milk. Next time around, I would probably add a cup more of either liquid to thin the custard out a bit and would soak the bread in a bowl, stirring occassionally before I transferred to baking dish. Side note: the chocolate chips melted as the bread pudding baked. I think this would also be great served with a raspberry sauce.

