Rating: 0
I made this recipe for Christmas Dinner and it was divine! I was inspired to make my own Triple Chocolate Bread Pudding after having an excellent one at "Harvest" in the Hotel Hershey, PA just a few days before. The reviews sold me on this one although I did make some minor changes and baked in a large casserole dish... I used Croissants (from Costco) at the recommendation of a pastry chef friend - one croissant yields 2 cups; I used Ghirardelli semisweet chocolate chips and Hershey brand cocoa; and added a few pieces of a Ghirardelli white chocolate baking bar coarsely chopped. I also used vanilla extract and brown sugar because they make everything taste better. And lastly I omitted the egg yolk for no good reason. I let mine soak all day in the fridge. This is an outstanding dessert, everyone LOVED it and we've been eating the leftovers for days. It is similar to a souffle but even better. Next time I will make it for a New Years Eve party and serve in individual ramekins with freshly whipped cream.

