Rating: 4
I am so glad that there is a chocolate bread pudding recipe that does not call for a water bath (horrible past experience with it). This was delicious and really easy to make. I'm not a fan of walnuts, but I kept them in anyway. For the chocolate chips, I mixed both bittersweet and semisweet kinds (Ghirardelli), which I think made for a nice flavor. And if you're in NYC and buy your challah from Zaro's, one challah loaf will give you enough bread cubes for two of these recipes. (and a trick I picked up from Dorie Greenspan's book: if you have fresh bread and you want to make them "stale," put them in an oven at 350F for about 10 minutes.) oh, and I didn't have ramekins, so I used a small enameled roasting dish. The 1st batch, I kept it in for 45 minutes. The 2nd batch, I kept it in for about 55 minutes. Either way, it tasted good. No complaints from anyone.

